# Blog Page

A full-featured blog platform built with Django, containerized with Docker, and served through Nginx. Supports user authentication, markdown-formatted posts, comments, likes, and newsletter subscriptions.

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|---|---|
| Backend | Django 4.0.3, Python 3.9 |
| Database | PostgreSQL 13 |
| Web Server | Gunicorn 20.1.0 |
| Reverse Proxy | Nginx 1.21 |
| Frontend | Bootstrap 5.1.3, Font Awesome 6, Animate.css |
| Markdown | django-markdownx, django-markdownify |
| Containerization | Docker, Docker Compose |

## Features

- Create, edit, and publish blog posts with Markdown support
- User registration, login, and profile management
- Post comments with moderation (approval system)
- Like/unlike posts via AJAX (no page reload)
- Newsletter email subscription
- Django admin panel with advanced post editor
- Particle network background animation and scroll effects
- Fully responsive design

## Project Structure

```
blog-page/
├── docker-compose.yml
├── Dockerfile
├── requirements.txt
├── nginx/
│   └── nginx.conf
└── django_blog/
    ├── manage.py
    ├── .env.example
    ├── django_blog/        # Project settings
    ├── blog/               # Posts, comments, likes, newsletter
    └── users/              # Registration and authentication
```

## Getting Started

### Prerequisites

- Docker and Docker Compose installed

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone <repository-url>
cd blog-page
```

### 2. Configure environment variables

```bash
cp django_blog/.env.example django_blog/.env
```

Edit `django_blog/.env` and fill in the required values:

```env
SECRET_KEY=your-secret-key
DEBUG=False
ALLOWED_HOSTS=localhost,127.0.0.1
DB_NAME=blog_db
DB_USER=blog_user
DB_PASSWORD=your-db-password
DB_HOST=db
DB_PORT=5432
```

### 3. Start the application

```bash
docker compose up -d
```

The application will be available at `http://localhost:8080`.

### 4. Apply database migrations

```bash
docker compose exec web python manage.py migrate
```

### 5. Create an admin user

```bash
docker compose exec web python manage.py createsuperuser
```

Admin panel is accessible at `http://localhost:8080/admin/`.

## URL Routes

| Route | Description |
|---|---|
| `/` | All published posts |
| `/post/<id>/` | Post detail with comments |
| `/post/new/` | Create a new post (login required) |
| `/post/<id>/edit/` | Edit a post (author only) |
| `/post/<id>/like/` | Toggle like via AJAX |
| `/newsletter/signup/` | Newsletter subscription |
| `/register/` | User registration |
| `/login/` | User login |
| `/admin/` | Django admin interface |

## Data Models

- **Post** — title, content, author, published date
- **Comment** — text, author, post, approval status
- **Like** — post and user (unique together)
- **Newsletter** — email, subscribed date, active status

## Development (without Docker)

```bash
cd django_blog
pip install -r ../requirements.txt
python manage.py migrate
python manage.py runserver
```

> Note: Requires a running PostgreSQL instance with credentials matching your `.env` file. Alternatively, switch `DATABASES` in `settings.py` to use SQLite for local development.

## Docker Services

| Service | Description | Port |
|---|---|---|
| `web` | Django + Gunicorn | 8000 (internal) |
| `db` | PostgreSQL 13 | 5432 (internal) |
| `nginx` | Reverse proxy | 8080 (public) |

Static and media files are shared between containers via Docker volumes.

